  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ten patients 70 years and older having elective total hip/knee replacement surgery will be
      recruited to receive a continuous IV infusion of naloxone and oral tramacet for analgesia.
      Postoperative analgesia, satisfaction, side effects, need for rescure analgesia, and length
      of stay.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
